2026-03-05 TASK-001 Verify serverside rendering

Changes:
- Replaced the placeholder test with a Node SSR test that requests `/` from
  the Hono app and asserts full HTML output plus serialized initial state.
- Added `test:ssr` in `package.json` and pointed `npm test` to it so tests run
  in Node.
- Added `test/stubs/cloudflare-workers.ts` to alias `cloudflare:workers`
  during Node bundling.
- Updated `src/client/routes/contact.tsx` submit handler event type from
  `SubmitEvent` to `Event` so project typecheck passes.
- Marked `TASK-001` as `passes: true` in `specs/prd.json`.

Patterns discovered:
- Worker SSR tests in Node need an alias for `cloudflare:workers`.
- CSS imports in server-shared JSX can be handled in Node test bundles with
  `esbuild --loader:.css=text`.
- `app.fetch(request, env)` works well for server-rendering verification with
  lightweight Env stubs.

Verification:
- `npm run lint` passed.
- `npm test` passed (8/8 assertions).
- `npx tsc --noEmit` passed.

2026-03-05 TASK-002 Client side rendering

Changes:
- Added `test/client.ts` to run browser-environment client hydration tests
  using `happy-dom` in Node.
- Added `test:client` in `package.json` and updated `npm test` to run both
  SSR (`test:ssr`) and client (`test:client`) suites.
- Updated `src/client/index.tsx` to hydrate from shared `App`, read
  `__INITIAL_STATE__`, and initialize client state from server-provided
  serialized state.
- Updated `src/client/state.ts` so `State()` can accept initial route/count
  values from SSR hydration payload.
- Updated `src/client/routes/home.tsx` to render and update counter text from
  a tracked numeric value so client interactions re-render as expected.
- Added `happy-dom` to `devDependencies`.
- Marked `TASK-002` as `passes: true` in `specs/prd.json`.

Patterns discovered:
- Browser-style client tests can run in Node by bundling test code with
  `esbuild` and leaving npm packages external (`--packages=external`) while
  installing DOM globals with `happy-dom`.
- Client hydration should read route/count from the SSR
  `__INITIAL_STATE__` script to avoid boot-time route drift from URL-only
  initialization.
- For this Hono JSX setup, rendering explicit numeric values in route output
  avoids unstable signal-object string output across SSR/client hydration.

Verification:
- `npm run lint` passed.
- `npm test` passed (`test:ssr` and `test:client` both green).
